              },
              "free_text": [
                " Target contained 4.69g of Pu,",
                "0.632g of oxygen minor amount of 241Am, 237Pu and",
                "0.85g of low mass elements. Target was",
                "reported to be a powder of 239Pu, 240Pu, and 241Pu in",
                "the oxide form, presumably PuO2, contained in a 0.458",
                "+- 0.001g Al foil and sealed in a 5.358+-0.001g Al",
                "container. Passive measurements suggested the",
                "presence of additional low-Z material. An x-ray image",
                "obtained during the bremsstrahlung irradiation of the",
                "target indicated that the PuO2 was pear shaped,",
                "sitting upright in the cylinder.Gamma-ray",
                "spectroscopy was used to determine the isotopic",
                "composition of the 240Pu target. Target contained",
                "minor amount of 237Pu ( 1E-10 g)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Three high-purity germanium (HPGe) detectors",
                "were used to collect gamma-ray spectra, one positioned",
                "at 90 deg and two at 127 deg (one atop the other),",
                "relative to the photon beam axis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "BRST"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "Bremsstrahlung photons were generated using 3-",
                "MeV electron beam produced by a Van de Graaff by",
                "impinging electrons on a 102 mu-m Au layer atop a",
                "1-cm thick water-cooled Cu backing. A 20-cm-thick Pb",
                "collimator downstream of the radiator restricted the",
                "photon beam to a narrow cone with a half-angle of",
                "1.8deg."
              ]
            }
